==Month of Besshi (дЄЩе≠РгБЃжЬИ)==
In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|и•њжЪ¶}} year whose final digit is 4 or 9 (corresponding to the heavenly stems {{ill|Kou|ja|зФ≤}} and {{ill|Ki|ja|еЈ±}}), the month of {{ill|November|ja|11жЬИ}} is designated as the Besshi {{ill|month (calendar)|ja|жЬИ (жЪ¶)|lt=Month|lt_ja=жЬИ}}. However, the term "month" here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|жЧІжЪ¶|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Daisetsu|ja|е§ІйЫ™}} until the day before {{ill|Lesser Cold|ja|е∞ПеѓТ}}) as applicable.

==Day of Besshi (дЄЩе≠РгБЃжЧ•)==
The {{ill|selected day|ja|йБЄжЧ•|1=Senjitsu}} for Besshi is as follows.
===Selected Day (йБЄжЧ•)===
Besshi day is the 7th (final) day of the {{ill|Hando|ja|зКѓеЬЯ|lt=Hando|lt_ja=е§ІеЬЯ}} period.


