'''Yang Fire Rat also known as дЄЩе≠Р''' (hinoene (дЄЩе≠Р), heikanonezumi (дЄЩе≠Р), heikanone (дЄЩе≠Р), heishi (дЄЩе≠Р)) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}.

It is the 13th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}, preceded by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|дєЩдЇ•}} and followed by {{ill|Teichuu|ja|дЄБдЄС}}. In {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°М}}, the heavenly stem {{ill|Hei|ja|дЄЩ|1=Hinoe (дЄЩ)}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ}}, while the earthly branch {{ill|Rat|ja|е≠Р (еНБдЇМжФѓ)|lt=Rat|lt_ja=е≠Р}} represents yang water, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=зЫЄеЙЛ}}, i.e. water overcomes fire).

