It is the 13th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|дєЩдЇ•|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Teichuu|ja|дЄБдЄС|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°М|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the heavenly stem {{ill|Hei|ja|дЄЩ|1=Hinoe (дЄЩ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the earthly branch {{ill|Rat|ja|е≠Р (еНБдЇМжФѓ)|lt=Rat|lt_ja=е≠Р|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang water, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=зЫЄеЙЛ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, i.e. water overcomes fire).

