==Month of Besshi (дЄЩе≠РгБЃжЬИ)==
In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|и•њжЪ¶|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=и•њжЪ¶|4=zh|5=еЕђеЕГ|6=es|7=Era com√Їn|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} year whose final digit is 4 or 9 (corresponding to the heavenly stems {{ill|Kou|ja|зФ≤|1=Kinoe (зФ≤)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and {{ill|Ki|ja|еЈ±|1=Tsuchinoto (еЈ±)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}), the month of {{ill|November|ja|11жЬИ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} is designated as the Besshi {{ill|month (calendar)|ja|жЬИ (жЪ¶)|lt=Month|lt_ja=жЬИ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. However, the term "month" here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|жЧІжЪ¶|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Daisetsu|ja|е§ІйЫ™|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} until the day before {{ill|Lesser Cold|ja|е∞ПеѓТ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) as applicable.

