It is the 13th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|дєЩдЇ•|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Teichuu|ja|дЄБдЄС|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°М|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the heavenly stem {{ill|Hei|ja|дЄЩ|1=Hinoe (дЄЩ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the earthly branch {{ill|Rat|ja|е≠Р (еНБдЇМжФѓ)|lt=Rat|lt_ja=е≠Р|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang water, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=зЫЄеЙЛ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, i.e. water overcomes fire).

